1900971.text:
<color=#B0E0E6>Rules</color>
1. There are 3 modes of Path Not Taken
Training (Permanently open, but score earned will not count towards your total)
Weekly (Open during the event; rewards available)
Daily (Open the next day after the event begins; rewards available)
2. Players can save their team with the highest stage clear score for later use.
3. Players can retry the combat they have failed. Failing will also consume a challenge attempt.
4. Players cannot use Assisting Dolls in this feature.
5. Path Not Taken opens every other week and each opening lasts a week.
<color=#B0E0E6>Modifiers</color>
1. There are 18 modifiers for Weeklies, and 15 modifiers for Dailies.
2. Doll attribute-lowering modifiers of the same type are mutually exclusive. You can only select 1 of the 3 modifiers of the same type.
<color=#B0E0E6>Costs</color>
1. For each opening, Weeklies have 10 free attempts. After free attempts are used up, 10 stamina is consumed per challenge.
2. For each opening, Dailies have 5 free attempts. After free attempts are used up, 10 stamina is consumed per challenge.
<color=#B0E0E6>Claiming Rewards</color>
1. Earn scores through winning in Weeklies and Dailies. When the total score reaches a certain amount, players can claim Unique Equipment related items.
2. Only the highest Daily scores and Weekly score will be counted towards the total.
3. Players can claim Intangible Core rewards after fulfilling the score requirements for a stage.
4. Unclaimed rewards in this opening will be kept until the next opening of the event.
<color=#B0E0E6>Rankings</color>
1. Rise in the Rankings for Path Not Taken by getting a higher score and clearing stages faster than others.
2. Rankings will be closed when the event ends. It will become available again at the next opening of the event.

1900979.text:
<color=#B0E0E6>Rules</color>
1. Players will encounter different events in Intangible Barrier. Defeat the Boss to enter the next stage.
2. Defeating Elite monsters and Bosses will grant Blessings, which help deal with harder challenges.
3. Clearing Stage 1-2 will unlock the auto exploration function. Tap the icon Auto in the bottom left to activate this mode.
<color=#B0E0E6>Defeat</color>
1. Once defeated, players will have to explore the current stage from the start, and all the Blessings gained in this stage will be gone.
<color=#B0E0E6>Challenges Reset</color>
1. Intangible Barrier opens once every four weeks, lasting a week.
2. Intangible Barrier exploration progress and rewards reset at 04:00 on $parameter1$/$parameter2$ (MM/DD). The more nodes you pass through in a week, the greater your rewards will be.
3. After Intangible Barrier resets, you can choose the starting point (Beginning/Last). Choosing "Beginning", you will start from the very beginning and lose all Blessings. Choosing "Last", you will start 3 stages before where you ended last time and lose the Blessings gained in the 3 stages; The Blessings kept since the last time will also be replaced with new Blessings of the same amount and it's up to you to pick the new Blessings.
<color=#B0E0E6>Intangible Core Reward</color>
1. Intangible Cores earned can be used to redeem Unique Equipment at Shop.

1901376.text:
<color=#B0E0E6>Gameplay</color>
1. Story: Read through the story and win combat for points and item rewards.
2. Training:
After completing all of the Story stages, 3 different Training Stories will be available and refreshed daily. Read through the Training Story for rewards.
Only 1 Training Story can be read each day.
Each Training Story will reward you with a buff item for the first 3 times you complete it. After you have earned all the buff items, you will be rewarded with event tokens instead.
3. Normal Combat: The higher the difficulty of combat, the better the rewards.
4. Scoring: Complete all of Main Story and reach the required number of event points to view your score and claim rewards.
5. Mail: A gift will be given to players daily for 7 days.
6. Christmas Banquet: Claim stamina here at a certain time daily for 14 days.
7. Backpack: View the buff items you have obtained in your backpack.
<color=#B0E0E6>Event Time</color>
1. Event Duration:
[Main Story] [Side Story] [Normal Combat] [Mail] [Christmas Banquet]: Dec 20, 2022 - Jan 3, 2023
2. Rewards Claiming Duration: Dec 20, 2022 - Jan 10, 2023

1901377.text:
<color=#B0E0E6>Gameplay</color>
1. Story: Read through the story and win combat for points and item rewards.
2. Training: Unlocked after completing all of the Story stages. Each stage can only be cleared once.
3. Doll Stamina:
  Each Doll has 5 stamina. 1 stamina point is consumed for every stage cleared. 
  Dolls with 0 stamina cannot be deployed for combat. 
  Doll stamina is refreshed at 04:00 daily.
4. Boss Battle: 
  Boss Battle is unlocked after clearing all of the Story stages.
  Players can challenge it once per day to win rewards for no stamina cost.
5. Boss Battle (Hard): 
  Boss Battle (Hard) is unlocked after clearing all of the Story stages.
  It can be challenged any number of times for no stamina cost but players will only be rewarded for the first clear.
<color=#B0E0E6>Event Time</color>
1. Event Duration:
[Main Story] [Training] [Boss Battle] Dec 27, 2022 - Jan 3, 2023

1901564.text:
<color=#B0E0E6>Introduction</color>
Evil Return-Rebirth refreshes every Monday at 04:00 and has 1 boss every week. There are a total of 18 difficulties.
After the refresh on Monday at 04:00, the <color=#DC7DFF>Punishing 2</color> difficulty unlocks. The <color=#FFCA65>Nightmare</color> difficulty unlocks on Thursday at 04:00. The results are tallied on Sunday at 04:00, during which you can't challenge the boss.
When a difficulty is cleared, the next difficulty unlocks; the cleared difficulty and the time used will be recorded. 
Different rewards can be obtained after clearing different difficulties.
<color=#B0E0E6>Talent Development</color>
Every difficulty level cleared grants 1 Talent Point. Collect Talent Points to light up your Talent—the Talent only works in Evil Return-Rebirth. Your Talent resets when the boss refreshes.
<color=#B0E0E6>Rankings</color>
The rankings include the top 200 players this week and the top 3 players last week.
<color=#B0E0E6>Achievements</color>
Complete achievements to get rewards.

1901674.text: Under the stars, somewhere along the edge of the void, a stranger is waiting for the Witch to show up.

1901675.text: Hungry void monsters eye their prey, itching to devour everything in sight.

1901676.text: In the nick of time, the Witch is saved by a powerful girl.

1901677.text: Ella snatches the crystal orb. The Witch has no choice but to dive into the void on her own in search of Ella and her friends.

1901678.text: The "unannounced guest" in the void seems to know everything about the Witch.

1901679.text: After a lot of searching and fighting, the Witch finds Ella and the others. Now it's time to get out of here.

1901680.text: The girls are stopped by Nannar just when they are about to leave. It turns out there is something else going on in this place.

1901681.text: With the help of friends, the Witch fights off her inner demon. And now everyone can finally go home.

1901692.text: After a long trek, you finally arrive in the Kingdom of Muntenia before dark. Better find a place to stay first.

1901693.text: The cemetery has a creepy feel to it. A faint sound comes from the darkness, sending a chill down your spine.

1901694.text: The girls decide to head to Nocturna's castle. But there are monsters lurking along the road.

1901695.text: It appears the castle gate is guarded. There is no passing through.

1901696.text: Looks like the castle too has been invaded by monsters. First things first, take out those monsters.

1901697.text: Those twisted monsters have made their way into the library. Nocturna is trapped in there. She needs help right now.

1901698.text: The evil dragon summons more monsters to destroy the castle.

1901699.text: The gluttonous dragon is right up ahead. Keep up.

1901700.text: You finally see the familiar faces of Ella and Metamorphoses. Ask them how to get out of here.

1901701.text: You are surprised there are other people in this unholy place.

1901702.text: Looks like there is also someone else chasing down the monsters, and they are hiding in the dark.

1901703.text: With Catherine's help, the girls subdue the guards.

1901704.text: Turns out Nocturna is in trouble too and has ended up as a target of a strange person.

1901705.text: The lady tracking monsters in the dark finally shows herself.

1901706.text: Sanva explains why there are monsters here.

1901707.text: The evil dragon has finally been defeated. Peace seems to have returned.

1901708.text: The evil dragon destroys the seal and starts recovering its power, trying to cause more mayhem.
